# 🚨 CORE CONSTRAINTS (ALWAYS APPLY)
- **RAM Constraint (16GB)**: The host machine only has 16GB RAM. 
  - NEVER suggest or use `make run-all`.
  - Only spin up Docker services related to the specific task group (Core, Kafka, Spark, Airflow, App, Lineage, Monitoring) according to `warnings.md`.
  - Explicitly define `mem_limit` in any new docker-compose definitions.
- **Zero-Cost Strategy**: 
  - The project relies on AWS/GCP Always-Free tiers and 100% open-source tools. 
  - DO NOT suggest or integrate paid APIs, proxy services, or external managed services outside of the approved list.
- **Tech Stack Freeze**: 
  - **Allowed**: Python, SQL, Bash, Docker, K8s, PostgreSQL, MinIO, Trino, Kafka, Spark, Airflow, dbt, Redis, Vault, Marquez, MLflow, Nessie, Streamlit, JupyterLab.
  - DO NOT introduce new frameworks, databases, or workflow engines without explicit human approval.
- **Verification First**: After writing code or shell scripts, tell the user exactly how to verify it works.
